Phillip Schutte and Pieter Doorewaard have been found guilty of murdering 15-year-old Matlhomola Mosweu in Coligny on 20 April last year by the North West High Court in Mahikeng. The duo maintained their innocence, saying the teenager had jumped off their bakkie on their way to the police station, after apprehending him for having allegedly stolen sunflowers. Watch video below: 